      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAPTAINS RUSH (3) missed by just a head first up then suffered interference and broke last start so did well to clock in midfield. Race fit and draws well so has winning claims. SHIFFRIN (2) is a daughter of leading sire Captaintreacherous on debut for Andy Gath. Can enjoy an economical run from this draw and should be well educated following a series of solid trials. Anticipating a bright start to her career. CAMERINA (4) was consistent last time in, ending her prep with a third at Maryborough from a tricky draw. Capable of a forward showing while fresh. BUNGY (5) has been drawn slightly wider in each of this three starts so far, highlighted by a debut second at Ballarat. Can be competitive.",
